        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 16 at 8:47AM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 847 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Shunk, or 7 miles southeast of Canton, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 35 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Towanda, West Franklin, Troy, Wilmot, Hollenback, West Burlington,
Wyalusing, Monroe, Laceyville, and New Albany.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
